## Article

```catala
declaration f
  content boolean
  depends on x content integer
  equals
    if x = 0 then false else true

declaration scope ScopeA:
  input i content boolean
  output a content boolean

scope ScopeA:
  definition a equals i

declaration scope ScopeB:
  output a content boolean
  subscope scope ScopeA
  internal g content boolean depends on x content integer
  output res content ScopeA

scope ScopeB:
  definition subscope.i equals true

  label base
  definition a equals subscope.a

  label one exception base
  definition a
  under condition 42 > 42
  consequence equals
    not subscope.a

  label two exception one
  definition a
  under condition 43 > 43
  consequence equals
    not subscope.a

  definition g of x equals
    match Absent with pattern
    -- Absent : false
    -- Present content p : true

  definition res equals
    output of ScopeA with { -- i: f of 2 or g of 3 }

  assertion 42 = 3
```
